title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.1: COMMUNITY BEHAVIOUR CHANGE - HIV-AIDS AND CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: Output 3.1: Children, parents, caregivers and communities in target counties, urban informal settlements and refugee settings have knowledge and adopt desirable practices to prevent and respond to HIV/AIDS, violence, abuse and exploitation of girls and boys, and have improved service-seeking behaviour, which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 3 - Children and adolescents are increasingly protected from exposure to HIV and AIDS, violence, abuse, exploitation and harmful cultural practices, and benefit from increased access to prevention, care, treatment, support, justice and other services needed to ensure their physical, mental and social wellbeing.

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the ‘Spot it, Stop it’ campaign to end violence against children, reaching an estimated 3 million;children, adolescents and adults through radio, tv and social media. A National Parenting Manual was drafted in consultation with the multi-sectoral technical working group members officially appointed by the Ministry of Public Service, Gender, Senior Citizen’s Affairs and Special Programmes, as one of the evidence-based approaches in the National Prevention and Response Plan on Violence against Children. In addition, 13.5 million people were reached with integrated advocacy messages on the triple threat of unintended pregnancy, HIV and sexual gender-based violence amongst adolescents. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/01/2022
